text: "What works" in ML is an open question. Can one actually prove the correctness of results from NN? It's theoretically impossible to do because each time you run the process the results are inherently unique. There are much simpler ways to go about deriving insight from data. Be it classifying cat images, determining credit scores, insurance claims or peoples' preference for toilet paper. Processing power counts to the cost of running a system like this, and it's very inefficient IMV.
